The evidence with the title 'The pros and cons of breaking up big banks | St. Louis Fed ' says Limiting the size of “ too big to fail ” banks could raise the cost of providing banking services by preventing banks from exploiting economies of scale .  ... For example , in 2001 , the five largest commercial banks held 30 percent of total U.S. banking system assets , topped by Bank Of America, which had $552 billion of assets. 
